Dear Jeff, I have reviewed this situation with our Competition & Compliance Manager. The decision has been made that, after the grace period of this 2016/17 season, we must now update our regulations and align to the NGB recommendations. Therefore, in line with Hockey Wales‚Äô decision regarding weekend games, the short pile 3G surface will not be suitable for BUCS games from the start of the 2018/19 season. I have been on a hockey development engagement trip around Wales this week, and met with the Aberystwyth hockey club committees and Student Union representatives (cc‚Äôd). It is certainly safe to say that the facility change has had a drastic negative impact on hockey in Aberystwyth, both on the student union clubs and on regional clubs and schools who would previously have accessed the facility. I would also comment on the exceptional role the university club committees have had in continuing to make the most of this difficult situation, battling to keep the club competitive whilst also taking on the coaching of junior age groups and providing playing opportunities to high level school players to keep hockey in the city. My trip finished with a meeting at Hockey Wales with Ria Male (also cc‚Äôd). It is clear that there is a very strong desire across all parties to work together towards creating a hockey-suitable facility in Aberystwyth as soon as possible, and your active engagement in this discussions would obviously be much appreciated. It would be great to hear an update on the situation from your perspective, and if any thoughts/discussions have taken place on the University side around potential investment in a suitable facility? It is my belief that Hockey Wales will be in touch in the immediate future to try and start moving some of these conversations forwards via a meeting with interested/relevant potential stakeholders.
